# VINE-Agent: Full Architecture & Implementation Plan

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **No GPU required for POC.** Only a free [Groq API key](https://console.groq.com/) is needed to run the demo.

---

## The Three Core Problems

### Problem 1 — How are sensor + drone data encoded to reach the final LLM?

The key principle: **everything must become structured text** before the LLM sees it, but
the structure is meaningful — not a dump of raw CSV rows.

#### Sensor Data Encoding Pipeline

```
IoT Device (every 5 min)
  → LoRaWAN / MQTT  →  message broker
  → Kafka topic: vine.sensors.raw          (production)
  → OR: CSV polling / HTTP webhook         (POC sim)

  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
  │           Sliding Window Feature Extractor      │
  │                                                 │
  │  Input: last 48h of readings per block          │
  │  Computes:                                      │
  │    - mean / min / max VWC (soil moisture)       │
  │    - trend: rising | stable | falling           │
  │    - ET₀ deficit accumulation                   │
  │    - # hours below irrigation threshold         │
  │    - heat stress flag (temp > 90°F)             │
  │    - CO₂ anomaly flag                           │
  │                                                 │
  │  Output: SensorContextBlock (structured dict)   │
  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
              │
              ▼
    ENCODED AS STRUCTURED TEXT BLOCK:

    ╔══════════════════════════════════════════════╗
    ║  [LIVE SENSOR — Block A, Chardonnay]         ║
    ║  Window: 2024-07-14 00:00 → 07-15 23:59     ║
    ║  ─────────────────────────────────────────   ║
    ║  Soil VWC:  avg=22.4%  min=18.9%  trend=↓   ║
    ║  Soil Temp: avg=74°F   max=93°F              ║
    ║  ET₀ deficit: 1.4 in accumulated (2d)        ║
    ║  Threshold breaches: 14h below 25% VWC       ║
    ║  ALERTS: ⚠ IRRIGATION_NEEDED, HEAT_STRESS   ║
    ╚══════════════════════════════════════════════╝

    This block is injected DIRECTLY into the Solver
    prompt — NOT into RAPTOR.
    Why? RAPTOR requires O(N²) re-clustering on
    insert. 5-min sensor ticks would make it unusable.
    Historical weekly summaries DO go into RAPTOR.
```

#### Drone Imagery Encoding Pipeline

```
GeoTIFF upload (every few days, post-flight)
  → rasterio reads bands: NIR, Red, RedEdge, SWIR

  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
  │            Band Math Engine                     │
  │                                                 │
  │  Per zone (grid of ~50x50 px = ~0.5 acre):     │
  │    NDVI   = (NIR - Red)  / (NIR + Red)         │
  │    NDRE   = (NIR - RE)   / (NIR + RE)          │
  │    NDWI   = (NIR - SWIR) / (NIR + SWIR)        │
  │    stressed_area_pct = pixels where NDVI<0.4   │
  │    anomaly_clusters  = DBSCAN on low-NDVI cells │
  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
              │
              ├──► Level 1 (POC): NL Text Summary
              │       → RAPTOR leaf node (nightly rebuild)
              │
              ▼

    ╔══════════════════════════════════════════════╗
    ║  [DRONE — Block A, Chardonnay, 2024-07-15]  ║
    ║  Flight: Iron Horse West, DJI P4 Multispect  ║
    ║  ─────────────────────────────────────────   ║
    ║  NDVI:  mean=0.61  min=0.38  max=0.79        ║
    ║  NDRE:  mean=0.34  (mild N deficiency zone)  ║
    ║  NDWI:  mean=0.12  (mild water stress)       ║
    ║  Stressed area: 18% of block (NDVI < 0.40)  ║
    ║  Anomaly cluster: 3 rows, NE corner          ║
    ║  Status: MILD_STRESS | N_DEFICIENCY_RISK     ║
    ╚══════════════════════════════════════════════╝

              │
              └──► Level 2 (production/future):
                     image patches → CLIP encoder →
                     dense vector → Milvus/Chroma →
                     retrieved by semantic query →
                     vision LLM (LLaVA on NRP vLLM)
                     describes anomaly visually
```

**Why Level 1 is sufficient for most queries:**
NDVI/NDRE numbers *are* the agronomic signal. A model seeing "NDVI=0.38 in NE corner"
can correctly reason about stress. Visual patch embeddings add value only for
detecting novel anomalies (frost damage patterns, hail, fungal texture) that band stats
cannot capture. That's Phase 2.

